  pacing: "Pacing is fast to mimic the high intensity and rush of sports gambling"
  climax: "Climax is very well executed, as it is the most intense part of the movie (the final 40 minutes feels like an anxiety attack)"
  tone: "The tone is anxiety and sports gambling (mixed with comedy at some points)"
  final_notes: "This movie is the butterfly effect of Derrick Rose getting injured (Derrick Rose tears his ACL -> Philadelphia upsets the Chicago Bulls -> Philadelphia plays Boston in the 2012 NBA Playoffs)"
  overall: "Overall, an anxiety rush that is championed by an incredible performance from Adam Sandler and great filmmaking from the Safdie brothers as the movie\'s intensity mimics the rush of sports gambling; side note, this movie is the butterfly effect of Derrick Rose tearing his ACL"
